---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="About"
  active="about"
  description="About Ratul Dawar — Software Engineer at Blinkit, building data platforms and query engines."
>
  <section class="about-hero">
    <div class="avatar">RD</div>
    <div>
      <h1>Hey, I'm Ratul</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">
        Software Engineer at <span class="highlight">Blinkit</span> (Zomato). I'm passionate about
        distributed systems, query engines, and open source. When not coding, I'm reading research
        papers or solving problems on Codeforces.
      </p>
      <div class="btn-row">
        <a href="mailto:ratuldawar11@gmail.com" class="btn btn-primary">Get in touch</a>
        <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/ratul-dawar11/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="btn btn-secondary">LinkedIn</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="about-section">
    <h2>What I work on</h2>
    <p>
      I build and optimize data infrastructure — from distributed query engines to high-throughput
      storage layers. Most of my open-source work lives in the Apache DataFusion ecosystem, where
      I focus on Parquet scan performance, string handling, and planner optimizations.
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Contributing to Apache DataFusion and the broader Arrow ecosystem</li>
      <li>Running Rust experiments with benchmarks and flamegraphs</li>
      <li>Building data platforms at Blinkit for real-time analytics at scale</li>
      <li>Writing about what I learn — measured results, not hand-waving</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="about-section">
    <h2>Elsewhere</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="https://github.com/RatulDawar">GitHub</a> — code and experiments</li>
      <li><a href="https://x.com/ratuldawar18">X / Twitter</a> — short takes on systems</li>
      <li><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/ratul-dawar11/">LinkedIn</a> — professional updates</li>
    </ul>
  </section>
</Layout>
